# Environment Configuration Templates

## Backend API - .env.example

```ini
# Database Configuration
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:password@localhost:5432/device_test_db

# Server Configuration
PORT=3000
NODE_ENV=development

# Frontend Configuration
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Logging
LOG_LEVEL=debug

# WebSocket
WS_ENABLED=true
WS_PATH=/socket.io

# Optional: Database Pool
DB_POOL_SIZE=20
DB_IDLE_TIMEOUT=30000
DB_CONNECTION_TIMEOUT=2000
```

## Device Simulator - .env.example

```ini
# Device Configuration
DEVICE_ID=device-001
PORT=3001

# Backend API
BACKEND_API_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Simulation Settings
SIMULATION_MODE=enabled
CRASH_PROBABILITY=0.02
NETWORK_FAILURE_PROBABILITY=0.05
LATENCY_SPIKE_PROBABILITY=0.15
SLOW_RESPONSE_PROBABILITY=0.08

# Device Firmware
FIRMWARE_VERSION=2.1.0

# Logging
LOG_LEVEL=info

# Performance
HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL=5000
```

## Test Runner - .env.example

```ini
# Backend API
BACKEND_API_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Device Simulator URLs (comma-separated)
DEVICE_SIMULATOR_URLS=http://localhost:3001,http://localhost:3002,http://localhost:3003

# Test Configuration
TEST_TIMEOUT=30000
RETRY_ATTEMPTS=3
CONCURRENT_DEVICES=true

# Performance Targets
PLAYBACK_START_THRESHOLD=1000
API_RESPONSE_THRESHOLD=500

# Logging
LOG_LEVEL=info

# Reporting
GENERATE_HTML_REPORT=true
REPORT_OUTPUT_PATH=./reports
```

## Docker Compose - Environment Variables

### Production Configuration

```yaml
services:
  backend-api:
    environment:
      DATABASE_URL: postgresql://db_user:secure_password@postgres-prod:5432/device_test_db_prod
      NODE_ENV: production
      PORT: 3000
      FRONTEND_URL: https://devices.example.com
      LOG_LEVEL: warn
      DB_POOL_SIZE: 50
```

### Staging Configuration

```yaml
services:
  backend-api:
    environment:
      DATABASE_URL: postgresql://db_user:staging_password@postgres-staging:5432/device_test_db_staging
      NODE_ENV: staging
      PORT: 3000
      FRONTEND_URL: https://staging-devices.example.com
      LOG_LEVEL: info
```

## Kubernetes Secrets

### Create from env files

```bash
kubectl create secret generic backend-env \
  --from-env-file=backend-api/.env \
  -n smart-device

kubectl create secret generic device-sim-env \
  --from-env-file=device-simulator/.env \
  -n smart-device
```

### Reference in deployment

```yaml
env:
- name: DATABASE_URL
  valueFrom:
    secretKeyRef:
      name: backend-env
      key: DATABASE_URL
```

## GitHub Actions Secrets

Set these in GitHub repository settings:

```
DOCKER_REGISTRY_URL=your-registry.azurecr.io
DOCKER_USERNAME=username
DOCKER_PASSWORD=password
KUBERNETES_CONFIG=base64_encoded_kubeconfig
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://...
```

## Configuration Best Practices

### Development
- Enable debug logging
- Use localhost URLs
- Single database instance
- No replication

### Staging
- Medium logging level
- Use internal service names
- Database with backup
- Load balancer ready

### Production
- Minimal logging (warn/error only)
- Use DNS names
- Database replication
- Multiple instances
- CDN for assets
- Monitoring enabled

## Environment Validation

```bash
#!/bin/bash

# Validate required variables
required_vars=("DATABASE_URL" "PORT" "BACKEND_API_URL")

for var in "${required_vars[@]}"; do
  if [ -z "${!var}" ]; then
    echo "Error: $var is not set"
    exit 1
  fi
done

echo "✅ All required variables are set"
```

## Secrets Management

### Using .env files (Development Only)

```bash
# Never commit .env files
echo ".env" >> .gitignore

# Use .env.example as template
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your secrets
```

### Using Environment Variables (Production)

```bash
# Export before running
export DATABASE_URL="postgresql://..."
export NODE_ENV="production"
npm start
```

### Using Docker Secrets (Swarm/Kubernetes)

```bash
# Create secret
docker secret create db_password db_password.txt

# Reference in docker-compose.yml
services:
  backend-api:
    secrets:
      - db_password
    environment:
      DATABASE_PASSWORD_FILE: /run/secrets/db_password
```

## Performance Tuning Variables

```ini
# Database connection pooling
DB_POOL_SIZE=20                    # Connections to maintain
DB_IDLE_TIMEOUT=30000              # Close idle after 30s
DB_CONNECTION_TIMEOUT=2000         # Wait 2s for connection

# Memory limits (Node.js)
NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=2048"  # 2GB max heap

# Worker threads
WORKER_THREADS=4                   # CPU-intensive operations

# Rate limiting
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW=900000           # 15 minutes
RATE_LIMIT_MAX_REQUESTS=1000       # Per window
```

## Feature Flags

```ini
# Enable/disable features
FEATURE_DEVICE_CLUSTERING=true
FEATURE_ADVANCED_METRICS=false
FEATURE_EMAIL_ALERTS=true
FEATURE_SLACK_INTEGRATION=false

# Beta features
BETA_FIRMWARE_SIMULATION=true
BETA_ML_ANOMALY_DETECTION=false
```

## Monitoring Variables

```ini
# Metrics collection
METRICS_ENABLED=true
METRICS_INTERVAL=60000             # Collect every 60s
PROMETHEUS_PORT=9090

# Tracing
TRACING_ENABLED=false
JAEGER_ENDPOINT=http://jaeger:6831

# Health checks
HEALTH_CHECK_INTERVAL=30000
HEALTH_CHECK_TIMEOUT=5000
```
